\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid3234388 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Can I ask you first what your name is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 William Owen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What's your address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well - the Smithy, Tan-y-Bwlch. That's what they know me as. If you want to know the name of the house though the house is called Is Goed. That's the name of the house itself but everyone calls it the smithy however.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've never married have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No I haven't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 When were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 I was born in 1896.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Here. No, no, in Trawsfynydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How many years did you live in the house that you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I wasn't two years old when I came here. We came here in 1898. I wasn't two when I came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You haven't moved anywhere since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. The family have lived here all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember why your family made this move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, you see, my father was a - blacksmith and 
for that matter so was my - grandfather, in fact we've been blacksmiths for generations. The thing was that my father lived in Trawsfynydd but worked in Llan }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 festiniog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean in the smithy down -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, that's right. He worked as a - as a serv
ant to - David Roberts who was the blacksmith in Llan at that time. And the thing was at that time although there was a blacksmith in Tan-y-bwlch he wasn't a very good shoer. Didn't shoe horses well. And so my father came down from Llan Ffestiniog to the 
P
las to put shoes on the horses. And the horses from - of the home farm and from the hotels went up to Llan to be shod. And because this particular blacksmith didn't - come up to standard he had to go away. And then there were a lot of people trying for hi
s position but - my father got the job because they already - knew about him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I had three sisters. They're buried now. And I had four brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How many years were there between the brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well the thing was, they came - as families did in those days. There must have been two to two and a half years between them. But - but I was the youngest of that group but two smaller ones were born when we moved down here but they died
. And there was quite a few more years between them and us. And now there's only me left. I'm the last one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Could you tell me how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, that's difficult - when I was born - I wonder how old he could have been. About forty I'd say. In his forties anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh Trawsfynydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 He was a blacksmith wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did he have any other job before he became a blacksmith?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. He was a blacksmith.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did he have any part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No. Never. Because you see my brothers used to - one after the other used to work with him. Yes, obvio
usly and being self employed it was different. And - oh yes, and anyway there was much more work at that - he had much more work to do than he was able to that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about your mother, do you remember how old she was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well she must have been, you know, between thirty-five and forty - since I was the last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Traws - Trawsfynydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did she have a job before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - she must have been some form of - service, 
as a servant, as people - women were in those days. An I'm sure it must have been some form of - farm servant as they were in those days. The things is that I have to go by hearsay really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did she work at all after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, she couldn't. She had enough work with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And she didn't have any part time jobs either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How many rooms were in your house both at Trawsfynydd and the house here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - I can't tell you about Trawsynydd. But
 here, let me see, there were one, two, three, four, five bedrooms here. But one was very small, but it was, you know, big enough for children. And we made that one into one with another one afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about receptions rooms, front room where you'd invite visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh the - the visitors were welcomed in the kitchen. Yes, there was the kitchen and a back kitchen and a - pantry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was there anyone apart from your parents and brothers and sisters living in the house with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No, none at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother have anyone in to help with the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. Because as far as I remember my sisters was all - was always with her here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was any washing sent out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No none. Everything was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother or father sew or mend clothes for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, plenty I'm sure, plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, not my father. My mother and sisters did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about clothes - did you have new clothes or secondhand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 We had new clothes when it was possible. And when it was time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Where did you buy these clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh I mainly got them in Llan Ffestiniog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was there any special time at which you went to get clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh no, only when we needed to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about the position with shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh it was just the same as the clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your father help your mother at all with jobs around the house like cleaning and cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - no. You know, the thing was I had - had sisters. A
nd my father and brothers had - you know - enough work of their own so - everybody had their own work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your father do any of the decorating or repairing of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean he didn't repair the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, 
no, and I'll tell you why. It's because the house came under auspices of the - estate. And the estate looked after everything in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did he help you as children at all with putting on your clothes or giving you baths, reading to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh
 - well, you know, we were brought up exactly the same as today. Except that life was very different then. There weren't so many luxuries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your father ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, he did. And my mother too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes, specially the younger ones if he was going somewhere. And if we wanted to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did he look after you when your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes. And the other thing is about his - authority. He - he never hit us. He only had to look at us. And we listened to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have any jobs around the house, did you help your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes, I mean everybody had their work. For instance if - chopping wood and getting - coal for the fire was y
our job you had to see to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And then the others had jobs too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, and we sort of graduated from one job to the other as - brothers - older brothers went out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you continue to do these jobs after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, yes
. 'Cos you see the thing was for each one of us, and this is one of the advantages for me today, each one of us boys had to learn, you know - sufficient cooking and to look after ourselves. Anything from washing the floor upwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 In your family did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did the younger children ever help the older children with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, in - in every way, as in any family. But then you couldn't really expec
t young children to do very much. It was the others that had to look after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have to go to bed at any particular time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 About what time did you have to go when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I mean that totally depended on how old you were. You went to bed at seven or eight o'clock depending on your age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother put you to bed or your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well the thing was it really depended on who - upon who was free. I mean, if my mother was - had a lot of wo
rk to do and my - sisters weren't available then my father did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How old were you when you went to bed on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Going to bed on my own? Oh well I was going to bed on my own before I went to school. You know, when I was four - five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you share your bedroom with anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Sometimes there was this little bed for me but then - other times I shared with a brother. And then there was always someone there looking after - looking after you. Yes, I shared my bedroom with my brother to start with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Your mother and father had a separate room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, they had their own room. And - my sisters had another room again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have a special room for having baths in or did you just have a tub in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How often did you have to have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh well that totally depended on what one looked like. I mean, we might have the one - have one on alternate days. Every other day I mean, if we got very dirty. But it - it was a rule that we had one once a week. Even if we were - if we were dirty or not.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, we had those - we had a rule about those. Every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 In what room did your family have their meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - in the kitchen. All together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was there any time when you ate in another room, on a special occasion or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - let me see. Yes, when it was very hot in the summer we used to - eat in the back kitchen, because it was cooler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother do all her cooking in the back kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did she use to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - a coal fire. An open fire. An open fire range with a - with a - an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 
oven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 . But then there was this other thing which I still used after I started work. This was th
e big brick oven which we had - in - in the back kitchen. Which is still there. Bricks with - sheets inside. Metal sheets presumably. And that was where she baked - bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I mean I had to go to school in Ma
entwrog. You are talking about me as a child aren't you? And I had to be there by nine and I had to walk all the way and no one was going to carry me. So surely I had my breakfast very soon after eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were the other members of the family present at that time too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, they'd already gone to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What time did they have their breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well - wait, wait, I must explain one thing to you. There was a little land that went with the smithy and there were two or three cows on it 
and so we had to get up to go and milk before breakfast and - then we came back for breakfast and then - then we went out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 to work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 . By eight o'clock. And then if there was a particular job to do in the smithy that - in summer - I mean it's hot enough in the
 summer and hot enough in the smithy. You know, we tried to do it before the heat of the day. You know, it might mean getting up at five o'clock. That is for a special job like whitewashing the walls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother get up at that time and make breakfast for everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. She did. They worked together. Yes, everyone worked together - in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What sort of things did you have as a rule for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well - maybe we had - porridge or something of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have anything different on special days like Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes, we did. I'll explain the period to you. It may be rather difficult to understand by today. Everywhere, in every house in this area I'm talking about now. Everyone you see kept a 
pig. And this acted as a reserve for the family. And then on the other hand, certainly in my case, with a bit of land we kept cows. And also three or four pigs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 
And three pigs would be sold and the other one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10688734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 kept, kept for use. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
And another thing that happe
ned at that time was that - they'd take a young calf, beef and maybe one or two or three people would buy - this calf together and salt it. And so therefore you had a sort of reserve of meat and then - and on a Sunday, on a Sunday we'd have fresh meat fro
m the butcher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 That was for dinner was it that you had the fresh meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, yes. But then we might have fresh meat in the middle of the week too. I was talking generally about families in this area, because I had an advantage over all the others 
because my family kept cows. And so there was no problem with butter or milk. I mean, nothing like that because I must have drank as much milk as any calf. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 
There was plenty of it you see, because they used to churn you see, they got their own butter.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What time did the family generally have dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh about - midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you come home from school for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No I didn't. No, I took my meal with me in the morning and I ate at school 'Cos I'll tell you a story, there was - an old boy wh
o worked on the farm and - his wife lived just up above the school and she was great friends with our family and one day she said to my mother, she was Mary - Mary Davis by the way, David Davis is her husband. And - one - one day then my - father - no my 
m
other said to my father that Mary had been complaining that William wasn't having enough food at school. So my mother had said, oh well he takes his food to school and - I mean he takes enough to school and he doesn't come back with any. And she said, wel
l
 I've never seen him not playing so it can't be possible that he's eating. And the out come of this was that I had to go up and eat at Mary Davis's house, which made it easier 'cos I didn't have to carry my food you see any more and I had - used to have t
o carry tea and sugar and things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about tea and supper, when and what did you have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16542616\charrsid10688734 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh well we had something different. Anything different. Well you see the thing was that because of the nature of - smith - a blacksmith's work he d
oesn't feel like eating a big meal at midday and then working after it. Because of the heat. And the result of this was that we had more - dinner in the evening because the thing was that if my brothers weren't working in the smith - in the smithy they we
re working somewhere else. And therefore no one would really want midday dinner and go and put shoes on a horse afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did you usually have to eat in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well, full dinner really. Yes, you know, potatoes and meat and - as mu
ch puddings you liked. For the reason that - as I told you before, we had plenty of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. Totally. They were home producers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, they made all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - we had enough - apples and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 plums}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  in the garden. This is another reason why I had - a sort of general advantage over everybody - every - other people sort of feeding habit. Because it was at hand, you know, it was
 on the land. And the other thing was, with the gardeners working up at Tan-y - Blwch at the Plas, they were really good gardeners. And the thing was - and they could - get potatoes and - vegetables. And the other thing with potatoes was that there was a 
- an enormous amount of co-operation in work between the farmers at that time. And, for instance we might be able to plant o row of potatoes or - in another farmers land but this would mean that in return we had to go and work in the hay for him. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 It would h
ave been all right if we'd just paid for rent for the row of potatoes but - days in the hay might take - you know, there might be man, many days in the hay, just for one row of potatoes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
And in the end it might have been cheaper to buy half a ton of potatoes. And so people became more self sufficient and didn't depend on each other to such an extent in the area. And there were few luxuries to go round in that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother make pickles, pickled onions or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did she make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, she made blackberry wine and - all sorts of wine, she was a good - she was an old hand at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did she make medicine at all for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did she make beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, she made a sort of - herbal beer. Called D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16542616\charrsid10688734 iod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 /D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16542616\charrsid10688734 ail}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  - made out of different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Your parents grew their own fruit and vegetables but did they buy any at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, if there was a need and things were short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about tinned fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh they - they didn't have much faith in them. Only for the reason that there were plenty of the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've already said they kept cows, what about hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes. Hens too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 The hens you mean? Well the thing was that my mother looked after the hens and the pigs and my - and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your brothers and father look after the cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I'd say we ate meat - in some form - every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about tinned meat, corned beef or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. Nothing like that. And I won't even eat it today, I've no faith in tinned meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you ever get any extra meat like rabbit from poaching?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - poaching. The thing w
as about Tan-y-Bwlch at that time - and the time - and that was how I was a - a little boy, a schoolboy, and there was a little stream down over there where they - where they put young breeding fish, the stewards put young breeding fish in - in the river 
t
here. And I used to go and fish in that little river but the steward asked my mother - to stop me doing this. And - but I mean if you went poaching - poaching salmon or rabbits, I mean, you'd be out on the road. And however much we wanted to we - we could
n
't, you know, we couldn't go and poach. But, you know, my father coming from Trawsynydd, he'd lived by the river there and he was quite used to it. And he'd been used to going hunting up in the mountains tool. But - once he'd come here and seen the rules 
- he gave up everything. And it set an example to the children too. It was a rule you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember your mother having less food at any time in order that her family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Goodness me no, there was plenty here always. Yes, there
 was plenty for everyone. I mean, that's what I mean, I had this advantage. There was plenty of everything of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were you allowed to talk at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No we weren't. You see - my father was kind but strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat or did you have to accept everything that your mother had cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - if we didn't like something we just went without. No fuss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What happened if you left food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well - they just thou
ght, you know, you'd failed, you - you just couldn't - couldn't - couldn't eat it. I mean, they didn't put pressure on us, then if we tried something and didn't like it that was it. And once she knew that you didn't like a certain food it was - wrong for 
you - and she wouldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 offer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 If there was something on the table, like the salt, that you wanted, were you allowed to ask for it or wait until it was offered to you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - oh yes, yes, we were allowed to ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Could you have a second helping if you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes. We could have as much as we could eat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they expect you to hold your knives and forks in particular ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have to sit at the table in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes, there was none of this, like I'm sitting tonight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about bringing toys or books up to the table, were you allowed to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 do}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, if it was free.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 I mean at mealtimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about leaving the table, could you leave when you liked or did you have to ask first or wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did the whole family sit at the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, everyone who was here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have the same places every time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Who served the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh my mother. The lady of the house that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 In what order were you served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh - well - I think - it was father first and then the older children and then the younger ones. But, I mean, everyone at together. But you see - in this meaning there - there was - a head of the house. It was like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Where did your younger brothers and sisters sit before they were able to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - I wouldn't know that 'cos they were all older than me anyway. They'd all learnt to eat long before
 I saw them. But I'm sure they were just like any other children, they would have sat on their mother's knees. And I mean once they'd learnt they came to the table. They always had a high chair It's still here today actually.
