\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 gone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 overboard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them? Did you have to show respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes. We did. The thing was, everybody did show respect. I never remember them asking for it. And the reason for this was that they'd given the children the - shown the children a good example and we followed them. I can never remember
 my father - parents showing disrespect to anyone, whoever he might be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they expect you to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well like brothers and sisters, you know, we could quarrel amongst ourselves, like every brother and sister that doesn't see }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 eye}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  - don't see eye to eye. As long as it sort of finished there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 If a child hit you were you allowed to hit him back, did your parents expect you to hit him back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - you weren't to hit first. But you had to defend yourself, oh yes, you had to defend yourself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you know what kind of person your parents hoped that you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - the only thing that I can tell you, they expected you to live - in accordance with the way in which you
'd been brought up. According to the principles by which you were brought up. And then it was up to you what you were going to make of yourself, but whatever you did it still had to be within the limits of the principles - by which you'd been - brought up
. They didn't go any further than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents think that some things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, as I was telling you, these principled, the principles of true life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did they think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Goodness - no. I mean
, we couldn't even answer back. If someone was older than you, and there were times when you felt like answering back. But, you know, you'd been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16542616\charrsid10688734 brought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  up with the rule that you must respect somebody older than you. 'Cos it would make you out of place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 When older people were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. We - we only - we were only to be seen - and not heard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 If you did something that your parents didn't like what happened? Were you punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No - we weren't - punished unless it happened repeatedly. They just old us not to do things. A
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've said already that your father never hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. He never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well, the only thing was, if you'd refused to listen - well - she was a l
eft hander too. And if you'd been carrying on moaning and groaning and she'd told you that you couldn't do something - she'd tell you to go. And - and you still didn't go and you still complained well, the thing she did - you know, when we were small we h
a
d a birch rod above the fire - and all she had to do was to pretend to go and fetch that. And the other thing she did was to slide her finger through your hair and grip - grip your hair. Try it yourself and you'll see how much it hurts. And I mean she did
n't really have to say much after that. And that was really the only punishment that we got.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did you feel towards this sort of punishment? Were you cross with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. I knew I deserved it by the time she'd gone that far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Would you say that you received the ideas about how to behave from both parents or from either one of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh from both. They both - agreed exactly about this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were birthdays from ordinary days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - everybody remembered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have a party and presents, things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, presents. Presents from members of the family. But there were none of these - these parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - pancakes of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Pancakes were the custom then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes, pancakes on a birthday. Yes, making pancakes was the - a special activity on a birthday. And the thing was that the welcome you got from people and what you were given to eat was very important, I've realized - I realize now, you kn
ow, having got older and looking back on it. Say you're invited to a house and you want to know exactly how - how you were in their esteem - one thing you're sure that you - you'll get pancakes, just simply because you've been invited. But if you were a s
pecial friend and they thought particularly highly of you what you got at that time was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 salmon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
, which was a luxury in those days. You got salmon you see. And to follow that you had jelly, red jelly. I suppose it was strawberry or something. And so if you got salmon and red jelly you knew that you were very high up in their estimation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about Christmas Day, do you remember your father or mother doing anything together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - everybody did things for Christmas Day, everything was prepared. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 
Yes, on the oven over there - Barra brith had been made. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
That's currant bread. And then there was the plum pudding. A lot of them would have been made. 'Cos you see there was this big boiler out at the back which we used for - for cooking the pigs will. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 It was a round boiler with a fire underneath and my mother and sisters would have made the puddings - and they'd put them in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10688734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5637547\charrsid10688734 cloths and - a cross - inside the boiler there were inner rods made in the smithy and they'd hang the puddings on these rods. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
And there would be seven or eight puddings hanging this way. Many more than we could eat for the - for the day, I mean some of them would be kept for - maybe a year. And - very often, me, when I got older, or my brother, would - watch after the puddi
ngs in the - as they were boiling in the evening. And so everything was prepared like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about musical instruments in the house, did you have any of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, we had a harmonium and an organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Who played these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - my sister played a bit. But really they were more in the world of singing than playing, I mean, they knew enough to make a noise.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Who sang in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh we all did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you make music as a family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, any sort of tunes that were around we'd sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about reciting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh I was a champion at that. Yes, and I've done a lot of recitations since then. I - I didn't praise myself at the time but I did a lot of it. But the trouble was, when I was about twenty I had to have al
l my teeth taken out - and have false teeth and the strange thing is I could never recite the same after that. You see the thing was that - that - air went underneath the plate. And - and that happened to me once, and I couldn't - cut the words in the sam
e
 way as I could and chew them over in the same way. And I'd be trying to say 'ess' or something and the wind - my breath or the air would go underneath them. And I nearly lost them once, they nearly fell out - but not quite. But I've - judged - recitation
 competitions a lot after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh ludo and draughts. That's what they had then. They didn't have any of the things that have come today, even meccano wasn't a
round. But they had - general games then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. We had a weekly newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, there weren't - there weren't any magazines, unless my sister got the odd one. You know, the - Home Chat or something like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember your mother and father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember them reading aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they read to each other or to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - they used to r
ead to us, before we were able to read ourselves. And you see, say we were altogether and everyone was reading - and my mother and father maybe reading the newspaper. Well - that's what we had to be dong then - that - we were supposed to be doing that, if
 they were reading. And then again if everyone was talking and making fun then I mean there wasn't any reading. But if there was reading then - no one was to soft of - speak across it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 Other
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 wise you'd muddle up the whole }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 show.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, I do. As I was saying, we buried to younger - two children younger than me. And since then I've buried them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was it a big funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, it wasn't. And for this reason, it was a private funer
al. Because we'd come from Trawsfynydd and the graveyard was in Trawsfynydd. And so it was private down here. And then there was the Oakley Drive. You had to get a permit to go up the Oakley Drive. It was - it was made private by Oakley. To - to connect w
ith the Maentwrog Road, and so you couldn't take a funeral up that way except with a permit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did people wear particular mourning clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. They wore - black clothes, and this crepe. I remember the crepe. A crepe armband and a hatband - which
 were worn by the men. Maybe if you still - you've seen those sometimes yourself. If they didn't go in for mourning clothes - maybe they hadn't been given permission to have mourning clothes. Then they'd wear the black armband and this showed just as much
 respect as if they were wearing all black clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember your family going to visit friends, neighbours and relations? Did they go often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. But not too often. Because they kept to this sort of saying that you don't visit your neighbours too often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you go with them when they went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh well that really depended on my age. And - speaking personally because I was the youngest - I had brothers and sisters and so when my father and mother went somewhere they didn't have to take me. The others were around to look after the younger ones.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember them taking you shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. When I needed something. They'd take - take one to see that - the clothes fitted all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Who did you generally go with - did everyone go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
No, I usually went with - with my mother. For this reason, my father was usually working. He didn't have any time to spare to do things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember going out with your father on his own ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, I mean if my father was going to do a job somewhere -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean on a farm or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, yes, or anywhere. And since I was the youngest and as long as it wasn't a school day he'd take me with him. And I'll tell you - no, I'll give you an example. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 There}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  was a schoolmistress, I won't name her, 'cos someone might }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 recognise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 her if I said her name. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 She}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 was a teacher in our school when I was in the infants - and she was a - a real - she used to pinch us, she was very cruel in that way. I felt her to be - cruel in that way because - you know, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 preferred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
to hit me rather than pinch me. But then again maybe it was her health that was the cause of this, and anyway she died. And she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 buried}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  here in Maentwrog, I know very well where here grave is today. And n
ow, in those days. I don't know if you've seen them and what they do in those days was - before the headstone had been placed in position - they'd make a sort of wire cage, exactly the same as the thing that they used to put - chicks on a long time ago, t
o
 stop them running out of the hen coup. And I remember well it was a Saturday and my father had been asked as usual to make one of these cages - frames. And so he asked me - since he was going to the village - if I wanted to go with him. And I'm sure you 
k
now I would have been - it would have been quite nice. I was sure it would be quite nice to go. And I had already been to - to bury her with the schoolchildren. Even though we were young children, the school children had all gone. And when I arrived at th
e
 - at the churchyard I found out that it was in fact her grave that my father had - was going to work on. And I've never been so happy with the thought that - as we came away - that my father had put a cage over her and she wouldn't be able to pinch me an
ymore. An I can even remember that today. I've remembered it for sixty-five years. 'Cos that's how a child is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember going on trips with your parents on special days like Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, if anything was going we used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you ever go away for a holiday with your parents - away to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 
seaside or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
No, no. They went. That was, you know, when I was older. And I don't think they did go - when we were small. And with the work and that, they may have 
gone away for a day or so. But once I was older and I'd started to work in the smithy well they'd go away for a holiday then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Where did they usually go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh they went to Pwllheli. That's where everyone went then. It was a seaside resort then.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Could you tell me how you spent your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 Saturdays}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well I used to work in the smithy up 'til about four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And then did you go out in the evenings and play or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes, and - even if - well after I'd started - working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about the evenings, did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes. Yes. Even after - even after I'd started working, and it was the era of the bike then. And if you felt like it you'd go up to Blaenau to the pictures. But then on
 the other hand you might just go visit the village in the evening. There were plenty of boys who sort of met together there. Nobody really thought of going out anywhere in the evenings except on Saturdays. Because in those days people worked long - worke
d a long day. It was a completely different period. Because of think of the people who worked in the quarry, I mean they went up to catch the workers train at about six o'clock in the morning. And it was about six or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night before they came home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they go up to Blaenau on the narrow gauge railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about Sunday, how did you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh in chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How many times did you go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Three times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you wear special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Sunday clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were you allowed to play games at all on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents think it was wrong to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well the thing was it wasn't - it wasn't the - custom. The rule. And the other thing is, to me, persona
lly, I mean, I grew up - I mean, I was born in - what was it - 1986 and it was 1904 - no, 1896 and it was 1904 that the revival broke out. And so I grew up in the period after the revival and things changed a lot after the revival. And the respect was the
n given to the - to the chapel and to religion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean this is all after the revival?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes. Because it was still very strong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was this a Methodist revival?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No, it was - it was later than that. It was the revival of Evan Rober
ts. And there was - it affected different denominations. Because we'd already had the 1859 revival and then - on. Now I'm talking about the 1904 one I'm telling it to you because it relates to behaviour on Sunday. And the general rule was to respect Sunda
y. Nothing could be done on Sunday. Only the essentials. I mean, we had to go and milk the cow, yes, of course, 'cos she wouldn't wait, and also to feed the pigs and things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Which chapel did your parents go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh, the Wesleyan chapel. They were
 called the Wesleyan Methodists at that time. Today it's called the Methodist church but then there were a lot of different - lots of different types of Methodist. Now the English and the Welsh Methodist are they same. They used to have the United Methodi
sts and the Primitive Methodists. There were five altogether but now they've become one and - just - are just called the Methodist church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother and father go to chapel every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes, every Sunday - and in the middle of the week too. We had these meetings in the middle of the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And you had to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you go on Sunday school trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, if one was going - I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were there any other social activities which the chapel organised that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes, there were - if there were other meetings and there was the Band of Hope. Yes, and the Band of Hope met every week. And when the Band - the term of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 Band of Hope}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  was coming to an end, you know, the winter term
. It was getting - towards the summer, they couldn't keep people there in the summer. Because people had to go to the hay and things. And so at the end we'd have an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 eisteddfod}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  and - with competitions and things. We'd singing competitions, recitation competitions, etc. And writing competitive essays and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you belong to the chapel choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, there weren't enough of us to make a full choir. But the things was that when there was an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 eisteddfod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  or something on - one or two of the chapels wou
ld get together to form a choir. That is in a small place like this. And I mean I belonged to all of those. As I told you the family were all for singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean they were singers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, they weren't singers but they were in favour of singing, they liked singing. But then from my mother's side they were - true singers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you say grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes. We said grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Who said grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh we were each taught in turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about saving prayers in the evening or before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, we'd have in the evening a form of family service, my father would read a few verses. Or else we would recite them. And then there'd be a sort of - a two minute silence. We believed more in that than sort of ordinary - praye
r. Sort of open prayer. It was a form of meditation. And in a way I think it was more effective. And these things are very - alive in my mind because my father was one of the people who - was - involved in the conversion, not the conversion, the - the rev
ival.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your father take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. And for this reason. His - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 judgment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  was - well - his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 judgment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 was - well, I - I'm not sure what his interest was or - or what - or his judgment }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 in fact}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 . But he felt that once he'd ma
de up his mind about something he'd stick to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 sort of individual}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10688734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, yes, exactly. He used to believe that if you were in a business you couldn't afford to play with politics. Because everyone was your custome
r. And then the day of the polling booths would come and - he felt that people should make up their minds about what they wanted to vote. Tory or Liberal, there were only those two in those days. And there was an old idea in those ideas in those days that
 if you went to the church you were a Tory and if you went to the non-conformist chapel you were a Liberal. There were only the two parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you think your father did vote Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh I don't know. He wouldn't say, he always felt it was private. He went to his grave before I knew what he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did you feel about this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh I - exactly the same, I - I completely agree with him - about this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. Nothing exceptional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And you've no idea what she voted either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
No. Because the thing was they had to go up to the Tanygrisiau to vote, 'cos that was the nearest polling booth, had to go up to Tanygrisiau through }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 Ffestiniog.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  And there would cars going with red - with blue and white ribbons on them. But they would go - both my mother and father would go independ}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 ntly. On the little train. Rather than get in any one of the cars. They were honest enough not to get into a Tory car which would carry them there, even if it di
d carry them there, and then vote Liberal. So they'd just go up to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 railway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  station as if they were going for a walk.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember your parents going to vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 1919? Yes, before the first world war. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
At this time in some places people felt that they were placing their jobs or their houses in jeopardy by voting in a different way from their employers, do you remember this happening or your father feeling this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 sort of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  pressure.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. It was here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were you actually under that sort of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes. We were. Yes. I remember old Oakley and he was a big Tory. Oh you couldn't get a more Liberal man in his sentiments but - he was a big Tory. And then there was the church in Maentw
rog, it was quite a strong church but they were all turncoats, because nobody asked you to contribute anything to keep - for the upkeep of the church because }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 Oakley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  paid for everything. And they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 didn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 have to pay for anything and they got work on the estate and a house. For going to the church. Do you see the old system. My father was completely }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 against}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  this, and he - but he did feel that this sort of pressure because when he came to - to live here somebody came up to him and said, well, you'll have to go 
- to church now. Or you won't be here very long. And he replied, I'll be a Wesleyan as long as I live. And - you know, he felt that he might have to move quickly but - he stayed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did either of your parents take part in any political activity besides that of a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, I mean, if there were any sort of good works to do, they were very willing to contribute to you know work in terms of working for anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 When your parents were not working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Not working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 I mean in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well there was one thing - really both of them were full of work. I mean, my mother had a lot do to prepare for her family and in the evenings she'd knit or something like that. Her and my sisters a
nd my father would do something else. And if he wasn't reading he'd be doing something. But then again he worked very late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh no, no. Except for things that I've already noted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean like the meetings and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 But there might be the equivalent of a coffee morning where they'd make a sort of functional like that to gather money for a certain cause?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, she - she'd go and - and - and she'd cook things for - for - towards a - a function like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 But she didn't go out to enjoy herself at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What time did your father finish work at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - well that entirely depended on how much work he had. Take the spring for instance when the farmers were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 ploughing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 . Well sometimes in the evenings they'd bring the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 plough}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  share to the smithy to get a piece on it. And it was over that that I turned rebel. Because I was supposed to be there to hit the iron, beat the iron. But there were only
 a few who'd do this, from over by Llanuwchlyn. And this they did in order that they could carry on in the morning, they wouldn't lose a day bringing the share over to the smithy. And if I had to be around to do that extra job of beating I'd miss out on a
ll the fun in the village. So the result was that if I ever saw any of those coming - I - I'd rush off and pretend that I hadn't seen them. I remember particularly one of them coming he was quite easy to watch because he had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  into Oakley Arms before he
 came down. And so I nipped off to the village. And - I mean since my father didn't have anyone to beat - the share had to stay there until the morning. And then in the summer it was the same, if a horse had lost its shoe - I - everyone would be perfectly
 welcome at five o'clock in the morning, even if they had to get my father out of bed. But - after five o'clock at night they wouldn't be welcome at all because he'd be very tired after working.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your father stay in at night, in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes, he never went away from here, except to these meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did he go to any clubs or pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Your mother didn't go either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your father take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. Well he might have done, I don't know, you know, when he was younger. But then there were - quite a lot of sports around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did he go to horse races at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No, nothing. I mean the races are pretty far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 I thought you mentioned something about the horse and dog show in Port }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 
Madoc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh the horse and dog show. Yes, but that was only a sort of annual fair. Annual thing. On the fourteenth of May. And it was the old fair in Tremadoc that took over from - that took the place of the Horse and Dog
 show. No, sorry, the Horse and Dog Show took over from the old fair in Tremadoc. It was like - it was a similar ting to the County Show today. I mean, it wasn't - it wasn't the race except of course like in every show there was a - a race at the end.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 He never betted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents belong to a savings club at all of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I don't know if they actually belonged to a club but they tried to save every }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 ha'penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Not even a club that would protect them if they were ill or save towards a funeral or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - the thing is they always made sure that they were insured. I mean that was the thing at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 This I presume I was a private insurance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  before the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean the 1911 act?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10688734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 o they'd pay the insurance company, the premium wasn't very big. And - it guaranteed that if somebody died a certain amount of money would be }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 forthcoming}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 . I mean, that was what was done then}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about your leisure time before}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 you left school, how did you get on with your brothers and sisters? Did you get on well with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, champion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was there any one of them that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean all the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. That 
is me personally, I wasn't - personally - more close to any one of them. But then there were two of my brothers who were particularly close to each other. But then again they were friends as brothers and - they didn't get on - they might not get on partic
ularly well but nobody could come between them. They might not hit if off completely. But - in relation to me, they couldn't - I couldn't do more for one than for the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 When you were a child who did you play with, did you play with your brothers and sisters or your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well the thing was, since the school in Maentwrog I was quite far away from the school. So I'd play with the boys that were nearer here. If the day was long enough. We'd play together around here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Where exactly would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh in the fields.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were you able to go into the houses of your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. Yes. When we were together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Which games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I suppose we played - hide and seek and things. And then after we'd grown up a 
bit most days we played quoits. And I was able to play quoits with the older boys because - my father or my - brothers would have made - light - lighter quoits for me to use. Because - I couldn't - I wasn't big enough to use such heavy ones. And so I coul
d go then, I had two or three quoits, they were made out of horse shoes, which made quite small rings. Yes, we played a lot of quoits in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I told you before that - we had to try not to. And then if you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 
kicking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  a ball and falling over and slipping well that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Could you play with anyone or did your parents restrict you to certain friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, we could play with everyone, there was no class distinction. They impre
ssed upon us that we should make no difference - no distinction between anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you belong to any youth organizations at all? The Boys Scouts or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh no, there was nothing like that. Anyway, not in this area. Because there
 weren't really enough people to form - such a thing. But I mean if there was something to read about the Scouts well I'd read it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have any special hobbies when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, I can't really say what my special hobby was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you keep pets for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you collect anything like stamps or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you do any gardening as a hobby, or was it work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh it was work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you go fishing at all? What about walking over the mountains or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, I'd ride a bike quite often. But take a Saturday afternoon, I'd go on a circular tour through Barmouth and home again through Trawsfynydd. And then we graduated to motor bikes as I got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you take part in any games or sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, a bit of everything. Football and everything. And quoits was the thing, I mean I played a lot of quoits as I said before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you go to the theatre, concerts or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 cinemas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, anything that was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 There wasn't a theatre around here was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
No, but I had the opportunities as I got older. I'd go on a trip or something to Liverpool. Yes, and I tried to do that because I mean for the reason that there wasn't anything like this goin
g in the area. But there was only the cinema then, the silent days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - wait a minute, the thing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 is}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  - I'll have to explain this to you. It was connected with my apprenticeship to be a blacksmith. If I w
anted to be a blacksmith and my parents hadn't been blacksmiths I'd have had to put twenty-five pounds down in order to be taught, and I wouldn't have got a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  of anything the first year. And I'd get my food from them the second year and then I'd get a 
little - amount of wages when I'd learnt a bit. But you see the thing was for me it was a family affair. And it was natural therefore as I was taught by my father, he taught each of us in turn, it wasn't - it wasn't necessary, as it was a family affair, t
o
 put the twenty-five pounds down. And - I had my food from the beginning. And what happened in fact was instead of getting wages I had pocket money. And then if you wanted to go and do something special, go away somewhere, then - they gave us - gave me mo
ney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did you spend your pocket money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh nothing in particular really, unless I was going somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've already said that nobody came in to help your mother with the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Because my sisters were with her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 If your mother was ill or had to stay in bed for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well, my sisters - looked after her. That is once they were old enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, none nearer than Trawsfynydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you go and visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, and they came down here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 In this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, everybody. Oh yes, they - they were neighbours you see, it's changed now, but in that time everyone was neighbours. Even in the h
aymaking season, there was only the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 hay cutter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  at that time, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 hay cutter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 and cutting the hay with a scythe. And if there was a small place with only - a scythe on it, that is one man with a scythe, then - neighbours would go and you'd have five or six
 people with their scythes helping the man. And - you'd have cut a pretty good field of hay in an evening. And then there was the women, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  wasn't a single woman in the village who wasn't used to using a rake. And they loved to come into the hay, for th
e reason that they had - were able to have a picnic in the field. You didn't have to - ask for help in - in those days, it was just there. For instance, if you'd already got your hay and the next door farm hadn't then you'd go over and help them get their
 hay in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your neighbours come here and visit you at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes, yes, the same. But - but as I told you, they didn't believed in coming too often. But they wouldn't hesitate to come if there was any need or - cause.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents share the same friends? Or did your father and mother have separate friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
No, no, I don't think it made any difference. I mean the thing was, and it may seem strange today, that there might - that there were - one or two - people who might go to
 the same church or the same chapel as one and one tended to be more friendly with them. And therefore if you wanted to say that some - they were friendly to some people more than others it was because of the - this - this - this reason, the chapel, was t
he community around the chapel. That's what I'd say anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 If your friends came to the house were they offered something to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they come on a special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, some - some of them if that was their habit. There were these - girls who used to come from Trawsfynydd and go down towards }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 Port Madoc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 and this house acted as a halfway house. And in those days they had to walk all the way. And I didn't see any one of them leave this house - house without being given food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were these friends of your father or your mother or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh they were friends of both, they'd both - they'd both been reared in the same - community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did any friends ever call on you without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, I mean there were those - I mean what would you call it - a surprise visit or something. Oh yes, I'm sure they used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And your neighbours came too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes. But the real thing with neighbours was that they didn't - they tended not to come unless they
 had a special message. A message about someone being ill in the community or in need of help. And - you know - either a neighbour would come past the smithy or - my - one of my parents would go - go past - go to see a neighbour, and find this out. And tr
y and arrange something for - this person or that person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
People say that at that time people made their own amusements, do you remember your parents going visiting friends and neighbours and playing games or singing with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 They}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  had - people had to in those days. And young people had to do it too. I mean we weren't all - courting. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  why we had such a community. Such a - a society round the chapel and I - you still hear it today about - Bethel doing something or other and Penia
l doing something else. And - you had to try and - and do things for yourself. And the trouble with today is that everything's done for you. You had to do it - yourself in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Some people divide society up into classes or groups, in the period
 before 1919 do you remember people being - there being distinctions between people in classes or groups?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well that depends on what you mean. Do you mean distinction - class distinction. Well the thing is, if anything good can come out of war - the thing that the 1914 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16284396\charrsid10688734 war}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  did was destroy some of the distinctions. Because everything - everybody had something in common then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean in the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, that's right. For instance, there was Mrs Inge's son who was very important before and then 
there'd be the blacksmith's son who - by that time was just as important as him, in the war that is. And there's another thing, you see. And another thing that - resulted from both wars, the 1914 - '18 and the second world war, was - because as you know, 
t
he Welshman has suffered a lot under foreign - foreign domination, and naturally therefore he suffered from a sort of inferiority complex and a lot of this inferiority complex has been eradicated by the two wars. Because in the war you could prove yoursel
f to be as just as good as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 any other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 . There was no difference between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Before the first world war do you think you could tell me what the different classes were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well it's difficult to say. Well, there was the top-notch. And then there was the
 so-called middle class. And then there was the bottom dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean working people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes. There were those three - three distinctions. And they depended on types of society that people - existed in. The circles they moved in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Which class would you say that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well, the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And other people in the same class as you, they were also workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes, and take these sort of people, the one's who've become managers in the quarry, they used to be worke
rs but - they managed to become managers - in the quarry. And those ones, they went to - and became members of the second class. And then there was Oakley, he was the proprietor - and that's how you get the three - three groups. And the workmen. That's si
m
plifying things though. For example let me just take the Oakley quarry because I've been talking about this area. Let's see, Oakley owned the quarry. And then there was the group that had become the so called managers, we'll leave the directors out of it.
 Because they're in their own class. That's right, the managers have become the middle. And the man who pulled the rock out and made the sl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 tes, he was the worker.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember being brought up to respect some people, and not others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I'v
e been telling you all along, everyone the same. But - I can remember when I was at school - the parson. One had to take ones cap off to the parson. Because he was one of the school managers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about taking your hat off to the Oakleys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, I mean, that goes without saying. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 
But the thing is, what I wanted to tell you was that I never heard of a schoolmaster telling you to take your hat off to a preacher. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Chapel preacher that is. But one had to do it to the - you see it was a school church - church school, and we therefore had to respect the parson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember calling anyone sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, that was an old thing. Oh yes, anyone that was taller from the shoulders up one had to emphasise that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in this way, touching their caps to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
No, the thing was I mean - the only person who did was old Oakley himself. He did it to everybody. And it was therefore natural to do that - to touch one's hat
 back to him. I don't know what it was, etiquette or something, but - you always did it to - or he always did it because maybe of his social standing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Who was considered important in the area, which people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well let me think, important people. W
ell - the steward - steward of the estate. Yes, he was a very important man because he acted as a go between and then there was anybody who happened to be a county councillor. I mean, he'd risen to a pretty good position. And then there was a lot of peopl
e who'd risen - who'd been - who'd gone on the local council. But that was more - open, open headed. Open to more people. People from a lower level became those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well the thing with them was th
at they had to be - gentlemanly, because they lived on their customers. But then there is this old saying in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
elsh which I'm sure - is still true, it still lasts - it's truth still lasts 'til today. Which is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 te}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
big at ei debig which means - like ones to lik
e ones. And so somebody in a certain social position would go to a person of a similar social position in the same line as him. Except that - I mean, they had - they had to be respectful to customers for their business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about the clergymen, who did they mix with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well they had to be the same. Yes, and the same thing applies here and I think a lot of preachers have been - misjudged, in my opinion. Because after all they had been to theological college. And - and if they wanted to get a prett
y good conversation going with someone, they had to - talk to someone with the same - the same interests about these things. And the problem was that people said that the - the preacher made more of some people than the others, and he shouldn't because af
t
er all everyone went to chapel. And the thing was, I mean, it was exactly the same for a teacher. And after all I mean, if I wanted to talk about the blacksmith's work it wouldn't do me any good to go and talk to a farmer. I mean, after all, I'd talk to a
nother blacksmith who knew what I was talking about. And - the same with a teacher or a - a preacher. I mean, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 tebig}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 at ei debig again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Would you say the same thing about farmers and employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 I'd say people who believed in a day of work. A day of work for going there. They received employment by being members of church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And what about chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - you know, as I was saying about that time - period - I don't think 
I really am the best person to ask about this period. I mean whatever the period was - I mean I didn't have to endure the brunt of it. I mean, there were more - other people who'd suffered a lot more. I mean, the thing was, I never had to work for - for w
ages under anyone else. Because there you had to take the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 brunt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 of it. And - this was because for the - for the reason that I was doing independent work. I mean, obviously you depended on your customers for work but I mean they depended as much on you. In o
rder to carry that is, I mean - you were more independent. Obviously there was nobody standing over you telling you what to do and what not to do. So I'm not, you know, really the person to talk about the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734  brunt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  of things. Oh well, that's O.K. then, and I'm telling you everything exactly as it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
We were talking about the difference between the people who went to church and the people who went to chapel, you've already said one lot were Liberals and the other Tories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, that was a matter of p
olitics you see. I mean, that was really supposed to be kept out of it. The thing was the people counted it though. Felt that you were a Tory if you went to - the church. I mean the thing was with the Oakleys and things, I mean, if you were - in some posi
t
ion of social standing you couldn't be less than a Tory. And therefore you went to church if you were in that social position. Yes. But then the thing was in Maentwrog a lot of them were turncoats as I say. Because if you went to church it cost you nothin
g. You didn't have to pay anything towards the cause. And you were absolutely sure of your work on the estate. More sure that is than if you were a non-conformist.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 In the are where you lived did the people in the working class have the same standard of living, within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. But then I must say there were some who did, even though they tried their best, didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 succeed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  in the working class. These were the people that needed help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 But you've already said that you felt that you had a better life than people who'd born the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 brunt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, yes. But I can't talk about the, m, I - I don't know. I mean, the thing is, it's applied - it's applied exactly the same today when the world's thriving, it means that there people are trying for one job. When a country's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 thriving}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 that is. I mean that's what's so odd. I mean, you know, it's sort of the unemployed. I mean, even in the quarry there was no use - there was no use in standing up for your rights in the quarry. I mean, the
 ones who did stand up for their rights there, well, they went over the tip. I mean, say they were working in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 Llanfrother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 quarry. Well, that was it, he got his cards. Or, I mean, there weren't cards, the sack. And there was no point in him going to the Oakley or anywhere else because - they'd have word beforehand that he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 rebel.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  There was no work for him. And what I'm saying is that I don't really know anything about that sort of brunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were there any families that you considered to be rough and others to be respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes, yes, I mean that was - I mean there were families who were rebellious. And the thing was - it - that was odd, was that it went from father to son. And this was it, I mean say someone had made - created a great deal of
 trouble. Had - I mean all people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 say is, what else can you expect. He was the son of so and so. I mean - oh it runs in a family or - I mean - there were things like that that existed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember a distinction being made between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes. In this sense. And this is what was odd, I mean, they had to - recognise the craftsmen. I mean, because he'd served a - an apprenticeship. But this is what was odd. Was that even in a quarry, a man who had served five years appr
enticeship, he'd only get tuppence an hour more than a labourer. I mean it wasn't recognised in that sense really. But then in another sense it was because the labourer. Well he was only a labourer. And the - they had to recognise the other as a craftsman
. And they did make the distinction, but to think that somebody had served a five year apprenticeship and the labourer had - well he'd been paid wages from the first day of work. I mean the difference was very little, but - yet it was - enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember if your mother and father had the same attitude to people of different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well - in this sense. Oh I - I'm sure they did in fact. I mean this is something I've realized as I've got older, but it was definitely something that should no
t be - shown to the children. I'm sure they did but - they taught us that everybody deserved respect. And your business is to respect everybody. And I'm sure they had I mean the same idea as I have today, I mean, I show respect to people. But - I mean - t
a
ke somebody who I think is a - a bit rebellious or - cross and nasty or something. I mean, you know, I just say, well - good luck to them or - every respect to them. He may be an old dog but - every respect to him. I'm sure that they did have a - but - bu
t
 they were sufficiently wise not to let the children see - any disrespect. Or listen to what - father and mother might say. Because what happens in - in many families who do talk about people in front of the children, the children go - I mean, they go and
 tell them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well, in the - this sense. I mean, she didn't - count herself as anything. But she was from a lineage. The - the lineage - the lineage of the Vaughans. And they'
d been - bit of a - they'd been a bit aristocratic. And what had happened over the years well who - there it is, but - but there was a bit of blue blood in her veins somewhere. Because it's odd you know, because you'd recognise the Vaughan family anywhere
 today, if you'd happened to notice or to look closely because of their stature. Yes, because even unknowingly to myself. Oh my mother, I mean, she - completely }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 unknowingly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 . If she was going somewhere, you could - she'd immediately - straighten - straighten
 up. I mean, she never really made a - made anything of it but - but it must have been something to do with her pride that she had - lineage somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember people who moved up from one class to another class, you've already said that workmen became managers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, I mean the stepping stones were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember anyone particular who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 Oh - oh yes, somebody who actually climbed these steps. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh yes, an uncle of mine. My father's brother. He went to Maenoffere
n and then he became a steward. And then my father had - another brother. And he's a different one because, to me, he was more of a man. A man of principle, you know, more of a man. He was not a man who was prepared to take his hat off to anyone. And then
 
- now take this uncle that became a steward. He had a son who worked in the quarry and he said to his brother, because the boys at that time who were learning about the quarry, had to look for sort of bits of stone to split - split for the other quarrymen
 - in order that they learn. Well, this uncle came past his brother and he said, Dick, remember Robin won't you? And - now, well my brother had been - no, the brother had been - getting pretty good stones at the time, good rocks - and - he said, well you}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12003663\charrsid10688734 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  son's the son of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 steward}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
, he'll get plenty of - of rock. There are other children here who need it far more. And so he didn't give a single rock to him. And it that's it you know, you - you were asking me. Well that's an example of two uncles of mine. The two types.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember anyone being called a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And do you remember why this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 I do. Because, you know, I've talked to you a lot about this respect because I've known people even when I w
as a boy. I mean, they might not say very much to you but I mean - everything was right. Everything's right. Everything was right. I mean, they got due respect. And there was something in them which you could recognise, but please don't ask me to explain 
i
t. I couldn't explain it but I'd recognise. I couldn't explain it but I'd recognise it today. And the trouble is a lot of people try to get an explanation for it. But there it is, I mean, what is it? The truth is I mean you can be a gentleman in rags. And
 the thing is you can't put a definition on it. I mean I can't and I've never heard anyone else able to. But the thing that's odd is that you do recognise it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, there was a policeman all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - he was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was he kind then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well - I'm sure he was. I'm sure he was. But even though I got beaten a couple of times when I was out making a row up in the village with the oth
er boys. But the thing that's odd is that you had respect for the policeman. And I mean he kept us on the straight too because you know if somebody. Did something wrong in those days well they went down to the village and - got a slap across the legs. And
 so if the policeman said something well - there's nothing we could say, we just obeyed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, it was. Everything on the estate was rented. And if you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, we saw him but it was through the steward that everything got - everything was worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How did you feel towards him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh well, the old boy was great. And Mrs Inge after him. I mean - you know, take people who actually worked on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 estate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 , well,
 in the period I mean they got small wages, but then on the other hand they only paid a very small rent. I mean they could live and - the fact - the estate did everything, did everything up. Whereas today the landlord looks after just the outside of the h
o
use and you look after the inside. But they did the inside as well, they kept the painting up and things. And I mean the great fact is I mean as I've grown up and realized the relationship between wages and rent - and repairs and that - the great fact is 
that I think Mrs Inge was paying them to live there. In the balance that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you ever remember your parents having difficulty in making ends meet and getting enough food and keeping things going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh no, no, they were O.K. As I told you they had - the little farm to keep them going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did it make any difference if your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, because each one of us boys and learnt his craft and - we - we could carry on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you ever have any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do yo
u remember if in your area if there was a person that was disapproved of, did the community have any particular way of showing this disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well there is - there's one thing which I have been nothing for you. I mean, it's quite likely that there
 were people which the other people would like to do without, the community would like to do without.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 But you don't remember people going and making a loud noise outside the house of the person which they disapproved of for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Rough music or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, I don't remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you ever remember them making straw men, like an effigy of someone and carrying it through the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, I didn't see anyone further than Guy Fawkes. No, I haven't seen anything of that nature in this area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have any lessons from your parents or from a private tutor or governess before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - as I was saying I mean - I was the youngest and I had brothers and si
sters apart from my mother and father. And so from the first moment that - could be A.B.C. was sort of taught to us. And so - and as you progressed I mean the others helped you along. And so therefore before you went to school at least you knew your lette
rs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - four. And you know I'd only go there maybe just in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 When you started going to school in the morning you had to be there by nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And you came home at half past there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What sort of school was it, a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, it was a church school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And you walked to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How long did it take to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well, you see, it's very difficult for me to say really, it depended what was - on the road. Yes, I remember that too when I used to walk down from TAN - Y- BWLCH I mean it took roughly a quarter of an hour, twenty minutes. But I remember quite well three
 
of us, one of us from Tavantrip and the other, Hugh Davis, who lives today in Llanuwchlyn, and there'd be something in the road - on the road. I remember when they were doing that stretch up towards the - the bridge. There was old John Williams on the ste
a
m roller. And of course the steam roller only went slowly, but John Williams let us take it in turns to drive the steam roller. And then of course we were late getting to school. Right. And then - there was a bell in Maentwrog school, and the schoolmaster
 
decided after this that three of us, each - all three of us should be there in the mornings to ring this bell. So therefore we had to be on time, you know, to ring the bell at nine o'clock. And so we went, you know, in order to obey. And in order that - o
ne of us shouldn't get - one of us shouldn't do all the ringing, he decided that all three of us should and we'd do it each one of us in turn. But what happened was that - we all three took }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 
hold}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  of the rope. And the second time the - rope broke. And so we t
hought we'd be all right after that. And by the next day, I mean we'd only been doing this for a day, and we thought we were pretty clear after that. I mean the rope was broken and - I mean, unless somebody went up into the belfry it would stay broken. On
ly by that evening he'd found three whistles somewhere and we had to go there the next morning with these whistles. It's strange you know, I can remember things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You said you took your own food to school, what sort of things did you take, sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, yes. Yes, that was when I was eating at school and I used to take a bottle of milk along too. And - and then afterwards I had to take the - my food pack and the bottle of milk up to Mary Davis's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did you feel about the school, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. I was - very happy at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How did you feel towards the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did the teachers emphasise anything in particular like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And punctuality and ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they expect you to speak pure Welsh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, but - yes, but - actually in my - time - most of the teaching was done in English in this school. N
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Was it to do with the fact that it was a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, not really. No - it was a lot of the people going there. There weren't - there wasn't that much Welsh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What happened if you did something the teachers disapproved of, were you punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - I mean - the punishment for me after I got older w
as - to send me to teach standard one. Yes, that was because they knew I hated this. It wasn't that I hated teaching the children in standard one because I knew the things all right. But it meant sitting away from the crowd because I mean I'd been you kno
w beaten enough times, but they found out that this - this other thing was much more of a punishment. Yes, they made me stand on one leg and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did the girls and the boys have the same punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well I can't say because I never saw - I
 mean, I never actually saw any girl being - beaten. I can't really say. I saw them being called out, I mean, and taken somewhere else and probably told off but never actually, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What sort of things did you get punished for at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 We
ll for the strangest things sometimes. Well - for instance - pens in those days were sharper than they were and longer than they are today. And so you could bend it like this and like this and like this. And so you could make it stand with just the - the 
s
mall point showing and you'd put his on the disk - the bench in front of you and then someone'd sit down and - oooh. And he'd jump up and then there'd be - who's done that? I mean, some people - but - most of the boys were very good at sticking together. 
But then - a few - or the odd one had more fear and he'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they ask you what you'd done at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they ever go and visit the school or visit the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh no. No. Because - there was only one time, and I was pretty young at the time, that I - or it was my sister that said that I'd been slapped at school and they asked me what I'd done. I said, I hadn't done anything. And they said, you 
never get a slap for doing nothing. You never get a slap for doing nothing. And if you say you got a slap for doing nothing then you can have another one for telling lies. And so I realized that if I said anything about being hit at school I'd get it even
 worse at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did the other children at school come from the same types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, I'm sure they pretty similar. There were all kinds of children. I mean, children from a farms and children from everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember there being any gangs at school, groups of boys being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 
mischievous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, the thing was - there weren't really any gangs. In my time t
here wasn't a sort of - wicked gang - at all. The biggest thing was, I mean, if there was a gang at all, about three - four or maybe five of us, we'd go up into the woods at midday. And the reason that - well even though in those days money was fairly sca
r
ce, somebody would have got a penny. And in those days I mean you could get - five cigarettes and holders, these Octanes - for a penny. And so we'd be up in the woods at lunchtime and I saw - some people becoming ill because sometimes - there'd be more th
a
n a penny between us and I mean it was a - a big smoke, and we'd have two packets. But we always shared them all. And I saw one boy who'd become ill and of course I couldn't leave him and it was nearly two o'clock in the afternoon before we went to school
. And the teacher knew very well what had happened. No, we didn't really do anything bad though, just the things that you expect children to do. And then I mean we were under the authority of the policeman as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you remember some children being left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - in the sense that there was - detention for some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Were there some children who nobody was friends with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, I never saw anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you go to another school after Maentwrog school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh I wasn't yet - fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Would you have stayed at school if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No I wouldn't. No, I mean, I had the opportunity, the opportunity to be anything else,
 the schoolmaster - felt that I ought to. But you know I don't know what it was, maybe it was hero worship but - my father and my brothers had all been blacksmiths. I mean, they'd come one after the other and even though the schoolmaster didn't want me to
 
leave school - and I'd been in standard seven for two years, I still left. And the thing was the summer holidays came and I wasn't fourteen 'til September but on the twenty-fifth of July I started in the smithy - as soon as the school had broken up. And t
hat was in 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you take part in any part time education after this, like night school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes. And the W.E.A. and everything. And - then there was the St. John's I was two years - with a gold }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 medalist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  from St. Johns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you regret anything about your education now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No. No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 Benefited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
 from going to school? Goodness me, yes. I mean you know some people reckon they didn't learn a thing at school. Oh but I - I cou
ldn't - really I couldn't say that. But then I mean the thing was that - I mean - as the head - the teacher at school realized, I was far from being a dud, and I could have become something other than a blacksmith if I'd wanted to. But then I mean - there
's one thing for sure, they've had a pretty good blacksmith.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 When you were at school did you work part time in the smithy with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes. But - you see, the thing was that each brother came one after the other. But as soon as I got stro
ng enough I used to beat the iron. Hit the iron, hammer the iron. And I'd be hammering in the evenings and on Saturdays. But really the main thing I did, you see I had this - stool and I used to sit up - near the mantelpiece and watch what they were doing
. That was, you know, what was wanted really. And so when I became old enough to do the work I know how to do it. And that was an advantage.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did they give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've already said that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, it - you know, it was a family affair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Obviously you liked the work or you wouldn't have chosen to do it, what exactly did you have to do in the smithy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What did I have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What exactly was the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - every sort of work, all sorts of work. There was fa
rm work, and then there was building work, for the estate and that. And I mean I can remember quite well there were seven - carpenters on the estate, and each one of them would do different things and I'd work on - with iron for them. And then there was t
he horses. And then there was - you know - was the - the shoeing of the horses and the paring and filing of their feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How many hours would you say you worked in a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - I mean - you know, my father was an early bird and if you were in the
 smithy after eight you were late. And I mean he'd been milking and that before that. And it also depended on how much work was in because - if - there was quite a bit of work to be done he'd say things like, oh we've got to kill this work by half - by mi
dday. Because you were fresh then, up until midday but you know, with the hammering naturally you got very tired. And that was why, and by the evening well - you didn't work late. But it didn't matter in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Obviously you didn't work on Sundays but what about Saturdays, when did you finish work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh - we worked up 'til four o'clock. That's when they finished on the estate too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you ever take holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well not - not really. We just went - somewhere - often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 And you obviously didn't have paid holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, but then you know if I was going somewhere they would give me - see that I had some money to go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 How much did they pay you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, you must remember that - you know, at this time even a craftsman wo
uld only earn about - at this time, about - a pound a week. And that was a pretty good wage. And then - I was only an apprentice but when you were able to do something that could - be - could go out - be sold - obviously you got paid more. For the reason 
that there was more money coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you feel that your payment was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well - I - it was all right. Because, I mean, you got a lot of something for a pound. That was the thing wasn't it. I mean, I'd rather have a pound today rather than th
irty-five pounds if I could get the same amount - amount of goods for it. It's only a matter of scale. I mean, that was the thing wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you get along well with your father in the work place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes, I - I worked with him you know well over twenty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did beginning this full time work change your attitude to school? Did it make you regret that you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've only worked as a blacksmith haven't you? You haven't done any other jobs. Looking back on
 things would you have liked to have done something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 In what sense do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Is there anything that you would have liked to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well no, not really because, I mean, for this reason, this was the work that I love. And I mean, there'
s no sense in looking back and regretting. There was a lot to look }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 forward }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
to, because, you know, you're improving all the time for the reason that - as soon as one thing finished a new thing started. You have to adapt yourself to this new thing. And there
's one thing, you know, for me - that if - whenever I get the call from this world - there's many more things left behind me here and regrettably I haven't got a wife or children, but - there are a lot of things here - that show I've been here and get - t
hat are going to stay. And the fact is you know I mean if you've - sawn up those things and you've made things - those things, well you've done something, I mean, something attempted, something done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've already said you served an apprenticeship, did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Which one did you belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Oh the National Master Farriers. Master Farriers you see, because I was registered in 1921, as a shoeing smith and a registered shoeing smith you see. Since 1921. That's looking back a long time now isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you take part at all in the activities of the trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes. Because you see there was the North Wales district - section. And then there was the annual general meeting. And - wh
oever was the chairman also belonged to the district committee. In Merioneth, in North Wales. And whoever was the chairman or the secretary of the district committee went to the annual general meeting. Yes, I've been - to a lot of places. Yes, I've been t
o
 the Isle of Bute and to Stratford on Avon, places like that. Because you see I got it passed in the district because I didn't see it fair that - we should keep the same chairman all the time. So I proposed it and it was carried through. That we change th
e chairman every year so that everybody could have their chance. And so therefore every time it was my turn to be the chairman I had to go away to the meeting. Oh yes, I've been in these activities you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Would you say that the interests of workers and the interests of employers are the same in society at large?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well, that's the same sort of question, you know, like the - other one I answered about bearing the brunt. You see, the thing with me was that I worked because I liked the work and the 
other thing was that it was a family affair. And carrying that tradition on. But you see, if I'd worked as a blacksmith and - and got nothing from it but the wages for being a blacksmith, I don't know how much interest there would have been in it. It woul
d just have been a day's work for an employer. But the thing was with me you know that for all the reasons I've said to you, I was interested in what I was doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You've already said that there was a great difference between craftsmen and other workers
, did you feel this yourself with the people that you came into contact with, did you feel that there was a big difference between craftsman and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, in this sense you see. From seeing and hearing about what a labourer was like - and 
finding out what the idea was about it - he was sort of different from me. Because I was a craftsman. And I mean whatever his opinion was of me - as a craftsman, I commanded his respect for that. And I mean there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 good}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  bit of difference between a craf
tsman and the others because you'd done an apprenticeship and it very much depends on what you are and with who you studied your apprenticeship. I mean you could turn out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 shoddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  work. But if you had pride in your work then I mean you could only produce the best. And it depends on people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 s idea or view of you, if you command respect in this way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Would you say that working has changed your general }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 attitude}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, yes, it has. In this sense - I'd say. You see, the thing that's important toda
y is - a few hours - a small number of hours and a big enough wage. And you see nobody asks about what the nature of the work should be. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  what the trouble is all about today. Production and things. I mean, the thing is they'd be quite prepared to
 raise the wages and - I suppose have less strikes, but - you've got to increase production. But then I mean the others want less hours, and more holidays - and more wages. I mean if you put all those three things together, well - there's something lackin
g. And you see - my attitude is - well - has changed a lot in that sense. Changed in comparison with the period in which I was in. And the thing was I mean apart from the fact that you - valued the nature of your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734  and - gave the best you could, I mean there was an enormous amount of competition. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7754924\charrsid10688734 
I mean, every village, Penryn, Blaenau, Llan Ffestiniog, Tan-y-bwlch, there were plenty of blacksmiths. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
And I mean the one that was going to get the work was the one that turned out the best work. And you know, in that sense, but I mean today, I mean, nobody asks about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 After you left school you went on living here with here with your parents, did it change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no, it didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about your relationship with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No, no. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about Sunday, did Sundays change at all or were they the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did it change at all when you started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you still go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you begin to take an interest in politics yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes, well I got an interest in politics but it's for - it's for me myself, within me. But you know, you remembered me talking before about mixing business and politics. I mean I've got my own politics, but you know that's it. It's dormant.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way as you had before you left school? Or did you do different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well, the biggest thing that I did in my spare time, you see I
 had all kinds of books and all sorts of other things when I've had the opportunity like the W.E.A. and the different ambulance classes. You see, I didn't give up reading or give up learning. Outside my work. I mean I'm still learning the work today. And 
I'll be learning it forever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Every night? Where did you go, to Maentwrog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, anywhere for a walk. To see the lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you make new friends at this time or were they the same friends you'd had at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
They are still the same friends as I'd always had. Even today. And there's this to say too, if a new boy came into the area - a farm worker or something - a couple of them have come to Maentwrog, and if you like to - thr
ow his lot in with all the rest of us, he was treated as one of us. So it made no difference - they didn't differentiate between him and us at all. He might as well have come from Maentwrog. But you see it was up to him. I mean, if he would stand aloof th
en - he'd stay that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh yes, very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You mean ones that I made more of than the others? Yes. And it's still the same now. He lives in St. Assas now
. St ASAPH You know, he's the sort of person - well we did more together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh we used to go anywhere. We might walk and climb up the MOELWYN. It just depended on - you know - what caught our fancy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well when you were young, yes. I mean before you'd left school that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 But what about after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well as far as I remember they trusted us after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did you have to be home at any particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Well - yes, there's one thing - yes, there was a rule like that I mean. And do you know, I mean if you had been away somewhere and you arrived back here late and one of them'd be on their feet still. Mother or fath
er. To see in what sort of state I was arriving home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What occupations did your brothers have, did they all become blacksmiths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Well - the eldest one, he learnt a blacksmiths trade. I mean, they all were apprentices. And he became a minister in 
1904. And then I had another brother, he was a blacksmith. And he started - after the other one went away to become the minister. But he'd been brought up a plasterer. And then there was another brother who came in but - he lost his health and he had to l
eave the - smithy and go out and the brother who was a plasterer came to the smithy and - because I was too young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 You said there were four brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh no, I meant there was four of us - four boys including me. And - then the - when I took over 
- in the smithy the - brother that was trained as a plasterer went down as a blacksmith to South Wales and then he came back and worked as a blacksmith in Maenofferen quarry until he died. He died there. And the brother that had to leave the blacksmith be
cause of his health, he died when he was thirty. And then it was up to me. And in fact it was me who was with my father more than any of the others, because in a way you know, I was - I'd just come in and it all followed on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about your sisters, did they work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 
Yes. Yes, they did. And one got married and one of them died - when she was young, the youngest of them. And the other one was - worked as - as a - a servant until the older one married. And then she came home to look after the home. And
 then she was with my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Did she stay with your mother all the way through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, and she was the one who lived with me until recently. Until a year ago in fact.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 What about the one who got married, what did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Oh he was a farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3234388 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 So only one of your sisters got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3104812 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2637935\charrsid10688734 Yes, yes, because the - the little girl had died young. Margaret that is.
\par }}